Senator Patrick Akinyelure (Ondo Central) has lost his bid to return to the Senate. Akinyelure lost at the People’s Democratic Party (PDP) primary by polling 58 votes. He was defeated by a political greenhorn and Senior Advocate of Nigeria, Adedipe Ifedayo, who got 82 votes. A former Ondo PDP Chairman, Clement Faboyede came third by garnering 57 votes.   NDLEA destroys 21 tonnes of drugs in Niger     Dismissed policeman gets life imprisonment for defiling…     Abia residents partially observe sit-at-home   There were however heavy security to bar thugs from storming the venue. In a chat with journalists, Ifedayo said it was the first time he would be contesting for elective office. “I thank God for this victory. I thank my party men and women who voted for me. It has been peaceful and very free. It is the PDP that has won and not Ifedayo. It is the party that conducts a free and fair election. My fellow aspirant should see this as a vote for all of us “We will require all hands on deck. This primary is based on existing law. What the law is is what they have followed. If Buhari signed the amended Electoral Act, it will be used in future election and not void this one,” he said.